      <summary>Why does the model say Prologis is so overvalued?</summary>
      <div class="faq-answer">Because a standard DCF relies on Free Cash Flow. Prologis' FCF is heavily depressed by its massive investments into new warehouse development. A DCF model assumes a company must pay off all its debt from this constrained free cash flow pool, which results in a low intrinsic value per share for asset-heavy, high-debt businesses like REITs.</div>
    </details>
    <details>
      <summary>What is a better way to value Prologis?</summary>
      <div class="faq-answer">Net Asset Value (NAV) and Price-to-AFFO (Adjusted Funds From Operations) are the standard methods. These metrics account for the true cash-generating power of the current property portfolio without unfairly penalizing the company for building new logistics centers.</div>
